{
  "day": 10,
  "key": "day_10_noah_rescued",
  "version": 1,
  "updated_at": "2026-02-01",
  "title": {
    "en": "God Rescues Righteous Noah"
  },
  "intro": {
    "en": [
      "As corruption spreads across the earth, one man remains faithful to God.",
      "God warns Noah of what is coming and provides a way of rescue for him and his family."
    ]
  },
  "blocks": {
    "en": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "righteousness",
        "icon": "verified",
        "label": { "en": "A Righteous Man" },
        "lines": [
          "Noah found favor in the eyes of the Lord.",
          "Noah was a righteous man,",
          "blameless among the people of his time,",
          "and he walked with God."
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "corruption",
        "icon": "warning",
        "label": { "en": "The Earth Is Corrupt" },
        "lines": [
          "Now the earth was corrupt in God’s sight",
          "and was full of violence.",
          "God saw how corrupt the earth had become,",
          "for all the people on earth",
          "had corruped their ways"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "covenant",
        "icon": "handshake",
        "label": { "en": "A Covenant of Rescue" },
        "lines": [
          "So God said to Noah,",
          "“I am going to bring floodwaters on the earth",
          "to destroy all life under the heavens,",
          "every creature that has the breath of life in it.",
          "Everything on earth will perish.",
          "But I will establish my covenant with you,",
          "and you will enter the ark—",
          "you and your sons,",
          "and your wife,",
          "and your sons’ wives with you.”"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "obedience",
        "icon": "construction",
        "label": { "en": "Faithful Obedience" },
        "lines": [
          "By faith Noah,",
          "when warned about things not yet seen,",
          "in holy fear",
          "built an ark",
          "to save his family."
        ]
      },

      {
        "type": "text",
        "marker": "blessing",
        "icon": "celebration",
        "label": { "en": "Blessing and New Beginning" },
        "lines": [
          "Then God blessed Noah and his sons,",
          "saying to them,",
          "“Be fruitful",
          "and increase in number",
          "and fill the earth.”"
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  "question": {
    "en": "What do you notice about how righteousness, warning, obedience, and rescue are connected in this story?"
  },
  "further_reading": {
    "en": ["Genesis 6:5–22", "Genesis 9:1", "Hebrews 11:7"]
  }
}
